<p>

Euranet members support the station with <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../852/42852.xml">
frequencies</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../751/234751.xml">
studios</link> and personnel. Deutsche Welle is to take care of editorial coordination, Radio France will manage finances and Radio Netherlands will operate the web portal.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref></p>
<p>

The project is primarily financed by the <control wordnetid="105196375" confidence="0.8">
<authority wordnetid="105196582" confidence="0.8">
<power wordnetid="105190804" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../974/9974.xml">
European Commission</link></power>
</authority>
</control>
 with <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../472/9472.xml">
€</link>5.8 million a year in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../719/146719.xml">
subsidies</link>, but the station is supposed to have full <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../049/6958049.xml">
editorial independence</link>.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref></p>

</sec>
